description:
Determines whether the the specified path points to a file.

Example:
1. "/home/user1/dir1/foo.txt"@0 received on `path`
2. true sent on `is file`

6edaa1a0-b372-4f07-8a36-5144bb2e22a3.description:
Receives the path to test whether it is a file or not.

Example:
"/home/user1/dir1/foo.txt"

(To keep the application portable use "/" as path separator.)
6edaa1a0-b372-4f07-8a36-5144bb2e22a3.name: path

7a6f90e6-76eb-46b1-bc2f-3d12b1499f1c.description:
Boolean value that indicates, whether the specified path is a file.

Example:
true
7a6f90e6-76eb-46b1-bc2f-3d12b1499f1c.name: is file

name: io/file/File tester
